#: ../../editing3.rst:2
msgid "Editing Recordings - Verse Markers and Rating"
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:4
msgid "Verse Markers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:6
msgid ""
"Verse markers are only available for when recordings are done in chunk "
"mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:8
msgid "Open the recording that has been edited and is ready to share with others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:9
msgid "Tap on the bookmark icon"
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:11
msgid "The Verse Marker window opens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:13
msgid "Notice the yellow playback bar on the bottom of the window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:14
msgid "The top gray bar has the number of markers left to put into place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:15
msgid "A verse marker is at the beginning of the recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:17
msgid "Tap the play icon to playback the recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:18
msgid "Tap the pause icon to stop the playback when it is at a verse ending."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:19
msgid "To add the verse marker: Tap the white flag on the yellow bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:21
msgid ""
"If there is another verse to mark: Continue to listen to the playback for"
" the next ending of a verse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:23
msgid "Optional ways of finding the correct spot in the recording:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:25
msgid ""
"Use the press-hold-drag action to move the playback forward or backward. "
"Have the verse division on the blue line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:26
msgid ""
"Use the press-hold-drag action to move the flag forward or backward on "
"the wave form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:28
msgid ""
"When there are no more verse markers to place – Tap the back icon "
"(Android back) found under the yellow bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:30
msgid "The verse markers are shown on the recording screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:32
msgid "Tap the SD Card icon to save and return to Project Management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:34
msgid "**HINT**: you might want to rate this recording before saving."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:40
msgid "Rate the Target Language Recording"
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:42
msgid ""
"To indicate the quality of the recording, you can add a star rating to "
"it. The star ratings are used for the program to determine which take of "
"a verse or chunk to use when compiling an entire chapter recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:44
msgid ""
"Tap the Star icon on the verse bar or in the top gray bar of the edit "
"window. The ‘Rate this take’ window opens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:45
msgid "Tap the left star if the recording is not the best – the star turns red."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:46
msgid ""
"Tap the middle star if the recording is fine but could be better – the "
"stars turn yellow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:47
msgid ""
"Tap the right star for an excellent recording – the starts turn green. "
"Only one take per verse/chunk can be rated 3 stars, because this "
"indicates the accepted take."
msgstr ""

#: ../../editing3.rst:48
msgid "Tap OK to save."
msgstr ""

